   Defeasance calculator Curious how much a defeasance would cost? Use our calculator for a quick estimate.  Go To Calculator   





Wells Fargo can help you with the complex process of defeasing a loan. Our defeasance clients include individual borrowers, institutional investors, financial institutions, investment banks, and third-party investment groups.    Why Wells Fargo?    What is Defeasance?    Upcoming Events     The Wells Fargo advantage   Experienced team. We have been conducting defeasance transactions since 2004. In the last 12+ years, we have closed more than 7,500 defeasance transactions totaling more than $88 billion. Of those transactions we have been the defeasance consultant on over half.   Simplified process. By acting in multiple defeasance roles on your behalf, we eliminate the complexity of having additional parties involved and therefore provide a comprehensive approach.        Lower costs. We offer free quotes based on real time pricing and our strong relationships with third-party vendors allow us to negotiate on your behalf and pass the savings along to you.     Defeasance is the process by which the real estate collateral securing a mortgage loan is replaced by government securities in order to release the real estate collateral, while keeping the payment stream for the mortgage loan intact. The release of the original collateral allows the borrower to sell or refinance the real estate.    Visit the Wells Fargo booth at these upcoming tradeshows: ICSC Carolinas Conference & Deal Making March 20-21, 2017  Charlotte, NC ICSC RECon The Global Retail Real Estate Convention  May 21-24, 2017  Las Vegas, NV   


